## Part 4 — DAX: Shared Infrastructure

### 4.1 Month-Selection Anchors (new in V3)

> **Dashboard-wide temporal model.** CM and PM driven by user’s Month slicer selection. Default = most recent complete month in data when nothing is selected.

```dax
-- Default month = most recent complete month in fact table
-- Used as fallback when slicer has no selection
_Default Month =
VAR MaxDate =
    CALCULATE(
        MAX( QUEUE_WORKER_APPLICATION[AYX_RUN_DT] ),
        ALL( QUEUE_WORKER_APPLICATION )
    )
VAR MaxMonthEnd = EOMONTH( MaxDate, 0 )
-- If the most recent date is mid-month, fall back to prior complete month
VAR DefaultMonthStart =
    IF( MaxDate < MaxMonthEnd, EOMONTH( MaxDate, -2 ) + 1, EOMONTH( MaxDate, -1 ) + 1 )
RETURN FORMAT( DefaultMonthStart, "YYYY-MM" )

-- Active month = user's slicer selection, or default if nothing selected
_Active Month =
COALESCE(
    SELECTEDVALUE( Dim_Date[Year_Month] ),
    [_Default Month]
)

-- Current Month anchors — driven by slicer selection
_CM Start =
CALCULATE(
    MIN( Dim_Date[Date_Key] ),
    FILTER( ALL( Dim_Date ), Dim_Date[Year_Month] = [_Active Month] )
)

_CM End =
CALCULATE(
    MAX( Dim_Date[Date_Key] ),
    FILTER( ALL( Dim_Date ), Dim_Date[Year_Month] = [_Active Month] )
)

-- Prior Month anchors — always one calendar month before _Active Month
_PM Start = EOMONTH( [_CM Start], -2 ) + 1

_PM End = EOMONTH( [_CM Start], -1 )
```

### 4.2 Rolling 30-Day Anchors (unchanged)

> Adoption screen only, for Active Users rolling comparison. Independent of month slicer.

```dax
_Rolling 30 Start =
CALCULATE( MAX( QUEUE_WORKER_APPLICATION[AYX_RUN_DT] ), ALL( QUEUE_WORKER_APPLICATION ) ) - 30

_Rolling 30 Prior Start =
CALCULATE( MAX( QUEUE_WORKER_APPLICATION[AYX_RUN_DT] ), ALL( QUEUE_WORKER_APPLICATION ) ) - 60

_Rolling 30 Prior End =
CALCULATE( MAX( QUEUE_WORKER_APPLICATION[AYX_RUN_DT] ), ALL( QUEUE_WORKER_APPLICATION ) ) - 31
```

